questiontext.text: A 21-year-old woman came to the General Hospital with complaints of crowding of her upper teeth. Extra oral examination presented flat profile. Intraoral examination showed maxillary anterior crowding. Normal overjet and overbite. Molar and canine in neutroocclusion. Model analysis, space discrepancy -3 mm in the maxilla. No narrowing of the jaw arch. What is the cause of the malocclusion above?

answer.text: The length of the jaw arch is the same as the length of the dental arch
The length of the maxillary arch is shorter than the length of the dental arch
The maxillary arch is longer than the dental arch
The mandibular arch is longer than the dental arch
The mandibular arch is longer than the dental arch

questiontext.text: A 25-year-old woman came to the General Hospital with complaints of crowding of the upper and lower teeth. extra oral examination presented flat profile. Intraoral examination showed maxillary anterior crowding. Normal overjet and overbite. Molar and canine in neutroocclusion. The dentist estimated the case required extraction of both the upper and lower jaws. To be sure, a model analysis is needed. The model analyzes that support the dentist's estimate are:

answer.text: ALD 0 mm RA dan -3 RB
ALD -3 mm RA dan -4 RB
ALD -4 mm RA dan -12 RB
ALD -12 mm RA dan -4 RB
ALD -12 mm RA dan RB

questiontext.text: A 21-year-old woman came to the General Hospital with complaints of crowding of her upper teeth. Extra oral examination presented flat profile. Intraoral examination showed maxillary anterior crowding. Normal overjet and overbite. Molar and canine in neutroocclusion. Model analysis, space discrepancy -3 mm in the maxilla. No narrowing of the jaw arch. What is the most likely clinical condition as the cause of the disorder in the above case?

answer.text: The size of the teeth of the upper and lower jaws is appropriate.
The maxillary teeth are larger than they should be.
The size of the lower jaw teeth is larger than it should be.
The maxillary teeth are smaller than they should be.
The size of the lower jaw teeth is smaller than it should be.
